caller_intent: Siggy is seeking resolution for a returned money order sent to Ascendo Insurance and is inquiring about the status of his insurance policies, expressing frustration with repeated issues.
resolution_steps: Brandy acknowledges the returned money order and explains that Siggy should take it to his bank to cash it.
She suggests contacting the 'food line' (where he obtained the money order) for further assistance.
Brandy confirms that Siggy's insurance policies are being processed and will be finalized next week.
She arranges a meeting at the office to handle necessary paperwork once Siggy has documents ready.
knowledge_required: Handling returned money orders and their cashing procedures
Customer service protocols for unresolved postal issues
summary: Siggy discusses a returned money order from Ascendo Insurance and updates on his policies. Brandy advises cashing the money order at a bank, confirms policy processing timelines, and schedules a meeting for paperwork. The call ends with mutual agreement to follow up next week.
